1
00:00:00,001 --> 00:00:03,469
Julia:
<i>Chester's mill is a place</i>
<i>like any other.</i>

2
00:00:03,471 --> 00:00:05,471
<i>At least, it used to be,</i>

3
00:00:05,473 --> 00:00:07,473
<i>Until we were cut off</i>
<i>from the rest of the world</i>

4
00:00:07,475 --> 00:00:09,341
<i>By a mysterious dome.</i>

5
00:00:13,114 --> 00:00:15,581
<i>Invisible, indestructible,</i>

6
00:00:15,583 --> 00:00:17,349
<i>Inescapable.</i>

7
00:00:17,351 --> 00:00:19,351
We're trapped.

8
00:00:19,353 --> 00:00:22,054
<i>We don't know where it</i>
<i>came from or why it's here,</i>

9
00:00:22,056 --> 00:00:24,323
<i>But now that we're all trapped</i>
<i>under the dome together,</i>

10
00:00:24,325 --> 00:00:26,091
<i>None of our secrets are safe.</i>

11
00:00:28,329 --> 00:00:29,628
Thanks again
for letting me crash here.

12
00:00:29,630 --> 00:00:31,130
My husband isn't here,

13
00:00:31,132 --> 00:00:33,132
But he'll turn up.
You'll see, barbie.

14
00:00:35,403 --> 00:00:37,770
That thing
is never going to go away.

15
00:00:39,473 --> 00:00:42,508
Oh, no. No.

16
00:00:42,510 --> 00:00:43,809
The pink stars
are falling in lines.

17
00:00:50,317 --> 00:00:53,252
Ride that dome!
Nice!

18
00:00:54,521 --> 00:00:58,057
Whoa, benny.
Dome ride was sick, bro.

19
00:00:58,059 --> 00:01:00,659
Paul: It's not gonna be okay!
 Yeah.

20
00:01:00,661 --> 00:01:04,396
This thing is never gonna go
away, and we're all gonna die!

21
00:01:07,101 --> 00:01:09,468
Dude. You're watching
that video again?

22
00:01:09,470 --> 00:01:11,136
I still can't believe it.

23
00:01:11,138 --> 00:01:12,805
Dan:
You weren't kidding
about that barbie guy.

24
00:01:12,807 --> 00:01:14,740
He took that cop's ass <i>down.</i>

25
00:01:14,742 --> 00:01:17,142
I wonder if barbie's,
like, black ops.

26
00:01:17,144 --> 00:01:18,377
Oh, my god,
your phone still works?

27
00:01:18,379 --> 00:01:19,445
So jealous.

28
00:01:19,447 --> 00:01:20,846
Yeah, the camera
and the apps.

29
00:01:20,848 --> 00:01:22,748
Just... No texting or calls.

30
00:01:22,750 --> 00:01:24,483
I miss texting.

31
00:01:24,485 --> 00:01:26,452
It's been, like,
a day and a half.
Whatever.

32
00:01:26,454 --> 00:01:27,419
Don't be judge-y.

33
00:01:27,421 --> 00:01:30,255
Dude. Show 'em.

34
00:01:30,257 --> 00:01:32,257
It's never gonna go away,

35
00:01:32,259 --> 00:01:33,392
And we're all gonna die!
Linda:
Paul, don't!

36
00:01:35,396 --> 00:01:38,464
Girl: The bullet just
bounced off the dome.

37
00:01:39,632 --> 00:01:41,266
Did paul mean to shoot freddy?

38
00:01:41,268 --> 00:01:42,534
I don't know.

39
00:01:42,536 --> 00:01:44,436
He was acting pretty crazy.

40
00:01:44,438 --> 00:01:46,305
I wonder what they'll do
with him.

41
00:01:46,307 --> 00:01:47,706
Cop killer's as bad as it gets.

42
00:01:47,708 --> 00:01:50,342
Especially a cop
that kills another cop.

43
00:01:56,783 --> 00:01:58,584
You in a hurry or something?

44
00:01:58,586 --> 00:02:00,586
I want to get to
the police station

45
00:02:00,588 --> 00:02:02,187
Before they walk
randolph in.

46
00:02:02,189 --> 00:02:04,590
What, you don't
like my driving?
I...

47
00:02:04,592 --> 00:02:08,260
Not that at all.
Just, uh...

48
00:02:08,262 --> 00:02:11,597
Nothing wrong with using
a little caution.

49
00:02:11,599 --> 00:02:13,265
I don't do caution.

50
00:02:13,267 --> 00:02:15,601
I noticed.

51
00:02:15,603 --> 00:02:18,871
Run-towards-the-fire
kind of girl, aren't you?

52
00:02:18,873 --> 00:02:20,873
I'm a journalist.

53
00:02:20,875 --> 00:02:23,675
I've got to find out
all I can about this dome

54
00:02:23,677 --> 00:02:25,811
So me, you and everyone
in this town

55
00:02:25,813 --> 00:02:27,813
Can get out as soon as possible.

56
00:02:27,815 --> 00:02:31,683
I've got a husband out there
I'd kind of like to see again.

57
00:02:40,293 --> 00:02:42,828
Man:
There he is.

58
00:02:42,830 --> 00:02:45,831
Deputy esquivel.
That was a pretty daring

59
00:02:45,833 --> 00:02:48,700
Thing you did, pulling reverend
coggins out of the fire.
Man: Killer!

60
00:02:48,702 --> 00:02:50,502
Just doing my job.
So, what, with
the entire

61
00:02:50,504 --> 00:02:52,271
Fire department
and half the police force

62
00:02:52,273 --> 00:02:54,706
Stuck outside the dome and
now two officers dead...

63
00:02:54,708 --> 00:02:55,908
What's your question?

64
00:02:55,910 --> 00:02:57,509
Can you handle this alone
until we find

65
00:02:57,511 --> 00:03:00,445
A way to get out?

66
00:03:00,447 --> 00:03:02,581
We'll be fine, mrs. Shumway.

67
00:03:02,583 --> 00:03:03,949
Long as we all

68
00:03:03,951 --> 00:03:05,584
Look out for each other.

69
00:03:06,519 --> 00:03:07,920
Murderer!
Killer!

70
00:03:07,922 --> 00:03:09,454
Let's get him!
Hey!

71
00:03:09,456 --> 00:03:11,223
Any more of that,
and I'll haul your ass in!

72
00:03:11,225 --> 00:03:12,457
Paul:
Hey, it was the dome

73
00:03:12,459 --> 00:03:13,859
That did it to freddy!

74
00:03:13,861 --> 00:03:15,761
It's gonna kill more
before it's done!

75
00:03:15,763 --> 00:03:18,330
Take him inside.
I can control this.

76
00:03:18,332 --> 00:03:19,765
Oh, so you're in charge now?

77
00:03:19,767 --> 00:03:21,767
Friends!

78
00:03:21,769 --> 00:03:25,237
I'm asking you all
to let the law do its job.

79
00:03:25,239 --> 00:03:27,606
The law did its job already--
killed an innocent man.
No, no, no.

80
00:03:27,608 --> 00:03:29,641
That was a tragic accident.

81
00:03:29,643 --> 00:03:31,443
As the town's
only remaining councilman,

82
00:03:31,445 --> 00:03:32,844
I will not countenance any kind

83
00:03:32,846 --> 00:03:36,481
Of frontier justice.

84
00:03:36,483 --> 00:03:37,916
Now, you go home,

85
00:03:37,918 --> 00:03:39,851
Clasp hands

86
00:03:39,853 --> 00:03:42,854
And pray for freddy denton's
poor soul.

87
00:03:42,856 --> 00:03:44,923
Go on.

88
00:03:50,597 --> 00:03:53,398
Ben:
Too bad we can't upload
that video to youtube.

89
00:03:53,400 --> 00:03:55,734
girl:
Excuse me.

90
00:03:55,736 --> 00:03:58,437
Where can a girl charge up
in this town?
Um...

91
00:03:58,439 --> 00:04:01,573
I have a generator at my...

92
00:04:01,575 --> 00:04:02,741
Your house?

93
00:04:02,743 --> 00:04:04,476
Ben:
We saw you

94
00:04:04,478 --> 00:04:06,478
At the fire.

95
00:04:06,480 --> 00:04:07,746
Uh, how'd you end up here?

96
00:04:07,748 --> 00:04:09,281
I just followed some kids.

97
00:04:09,283 --> 00:04:10,582
Heard 'em talking
about a bonfire.

98
00:04:10,584 --> 00:04:12,484
No, I meant, how...
I knew what you meant.

99
00:04:12,486 --> 00:04:14,786
I was on my way someplace and...

100
00:04:14,788 --> 00:04:17,656
Wrong place
at the wrong time, I guess.

101
00:04:18,658 --> 00:04:21,260
I'm not usually a mooch,
but without my music,

102
00:04:21,262 --> 00:04:23,795
I can get a little,
you know, super bitchy.

103
00:04:23,797 --> 00:04:25,764
Can I refuel at your place?

104
00:04:25,766 --> 00:04:28,467
Sure. There's no one
home except me...

105
00:04:28,469 --> 00:04:29,568
Cool.

106
00:04:29,570 --> 00:04:32,471
I actually need
a place to crash, too.

107
00:04:32,473 --> 00:04:33,672
If that's okay,
I mean.

108
00:04:33,674 --> 00:04:34,940
Oh...

109
00:04:34,942 --> 00:04:37,476
Well, I mean, I saw
you with two ladies.

110
00:04:37,478 --> 00:04:38,944
I thought you
were with them.

111
00:04:38,946 --> 00:04:40,579
Never seen 'em before.

112
00:04:40,581 --> 00:04:42,981
So...

113
00:04:42,983 --> 00:04:45,050
Cool to crash?

114
00:04:49,856 --> 00:04:51,923
Paul:
I'm sorry.

115
00:04:51,925 --> 00:04:54,860
Freddy, he was my partner,
and he was my friend,

116
00:04:54,862 --> 00:04:58,297
But he wouldn't be dead
if it weren't for this dome.

117
00:04:58,299 --> 00:05:00,399
You're gonna have to tell rusty.

118
00:05:00,401 --> 00:05:02,467
He'll understand.

119
00:05:02,469 --> 00:05:04,970
Like hell he will!
He's freddy's brother!

120
00:05:04,972 --> 00:05:06,571
What did we do to deserve this?

121
00:05:08,776 --> 00:05:11,076
Are you okay?

122
00:05:11,078 --> 00:05:12,744
Paul?

123
00:05:22,755 --> 00:05:25,424
I warned you, linda.

124
00:05:25,426 --> 00:05:26,792
I warned you what would happen.

125
00:05:26,794 --> 00:05:28,794
This is all
a misunderstanding, paul.

126
00:05:28,796 --> 00:05:29,928
No, it's not.

127
00:05:29,930 --> 00:05:31,797
It's the dome.

128
00:05:31,799 --> 00:05:34,633
It's making everyone crazy,
and it's going to kill us all.

129
00:05:34,635 --> 00:05:36,535
If the town doesn't
kill me first.

130
00:05:37,704 --> 00:05:39,438
Paul.

131
00:05:39,440 --> 00:05:41,473
Paul!

132
00:06:06,400 --> 00:06:07,866
Where were you yesterday,
junior?

133
00:06:07,868 --> 00:06:08,867
Nowhere.

134
00:06:10,637 --> 00:06:12,471
Whole town
pulls together

135
00:06:12,473 --> 00:06:16,608
To put out a fire.
But you?

136
00:06:16,610 --> 00:06:19,678
"nowhere"
to be found.

137
00:06:19,680 --> 00:06:21,513
Dad...
Shut your mouth.

138
00:06:21,515 --> 00:06:23,548
Mmm.

139
00:06:23,550 --> 00:06:25,016
People are looking to me.

140
00:06:25,018 --> 00:06:26,685
To lead.

141
00:06:26,687 --> 00:06:29,521
To stand up, like a man does.

142
00:06:29,523 --> 00:06:31,523
It reflects poorly

143
00:06:31,525 --> 00:06:34,159
When my son is awol.

144
00:06:34,161 --> 00:06:37,863
This situation,
it's an opportunity.

145
00:06:37,865 --> 00:06:41,166
All your life, I've provided you
with advantages.

146
00:06:41,168 --> 00:06:42,501
Opening doors.

147
00:06:42,503 --> 00:06:44,035
Like with the football team.

148
00:06:44,037 --> 00:06:46,538
Dad, I never wanted to play...
Point is

149
00:06:46,540 --> 00:06:48,039
You only get so many chances
in life.

150
00:06:48,041 --> 00:06:49,741
Do not squander them.

151
00:06:52,879 --> 00:06:54,880
What happened
to your face?

152
00:06:54,882 --> 00:06:56,848
Nothing.
No, what...

153
00:06:59,819 --> 00:07:01,887
Who did this to your face?

154
00:07:01,889 --> 00:07:04,623
This guy.

155
00:07:04,625 --> 00:07:07,826
His name's barbie, I think.

156
00:07:07,828 --> 00:07:10,495
He's totally insane.

157
00:07:11,631 --> 00:07:14,032
Nine years it's been
since your mother died.

158
00:07:15,735 --> 00:07:18,804
And still it's like
you're hiding behind her skirt.

159
00:07:21,140 --> 00:07:24,209
Best toughen up
now, junior.

160
00:07:25,478 --> 00:07:28,547
Don't you let me down.

161
00:07:34,121 --> 00:07:35,854
Phil:
Your dial's set to wybs,

162
00:07:35,856 --> 00:07:38,623
The only-- and I literally
mean the only--

163
00:07:38,625 --> 00:07:40,625
Source of news here
in chester's mill.

164
00:07:40,627 --> 00:07:42,661
Couple of shout-outs:
First, to everyone

165
00:07:42,663 --> 00:07:44,196
Who grabbed a bucket yesterday

166
00:07:44,198 --> 00:07:45,664
And joined
the volunteer brigade.

167
00:07:45,666 --> 00:07:47,999
Way to stay
civic-minded, people.

168
00:07:48,001 --> 00:07:50,669
And big ups
to the lovely linda esquivel

169
00:07:50,671 --> 00:07:53,672
for her daring rescue
of reverend coggins.

170
00:08:06,519 --> 00:08:09,788
I made you
some eggs.

171
00:08:09,790 --> 00:08:12,691
Figured you could use
some protein.

172
00:08:22,235 --> 00:08:25,237
I get it.

173
00:08:25,239 --> 00:08:28,073
You're angry, but...

174
00:08:28,075 --> 00:08:30,775
It's the dome
that's making you act like this.

175
00:08:31,744 --> 00:08:34,813
Nothing's making me act
like this.

176
00:08:36,616 --> 00:08:39,251
It's you locking me
down here for two days.

177
00:08:39,253 --> 00:08:44,556
Everything is gonna go back
to the way it was before.

178
00:08:44,558 --> 00:08:46,691
You'll see, ange.

179
00:08:46,693 --> 00:08:50,762
Soon as we get out
from under this thing.

180
00:08:55,701 --> 00:08:58,103
Has anyone tried going under it?

181
00:08:58,105 --> 00:08:59,971
People took shovels
and tried digging...
No.

182
00:08:59,973 --> 00:09:03,642
I mean... Way under it.

183
00:09:03,644 --> 00:09:06,011
Like through the cement factory
tunnels.

184
00:09:06,013 --> 00:09:08,847
They closed those off...

185
00:09:08,849 --> 00:09:10,715
After the flood

186
00:09:10,717 --> 00:09:11,750
When those kids
died down there.

187
00:09:11,752 --> 00:09:15,220
You and I still went down there
all the time.

188
00:09:15,222 --> 00:09:17,722
Walked through
the tunnels

189
00:09:17,724 --> 00:09:21,326
Till we came across
the town line into westlake,

190
00:09:21,328 --> 00:09:23,795
Hitchhiked back.

191
00:09:24,764 --> 00:09:27,832
Maybe you're right.

192
00:09:28,768 --> 00:09:31,236
Maybe...

193
00:09:31,238 --> 00:09:34,773
Things would be different
if you could find a way out.

194
00:09:39,345 --> 00:09:41,680
Maybe we could...

195
00:09:41,682 --> 00:09:43,748
Start over.

196
00:09:49,655 --> 00:09:51,122
I'll be back later.

197
00:10:02,935 --> 00:10:04,603
Rise and shine,
reverend.

198
00:10:06,173 --> 00:10:07,839
The hell were you thinking?

199
00:10:07,841 --> 00:10:10,108
I told you to find
the evidence and destroy it,

200
00:10:10,110 --> 00:10:11,977
Not torch a dead man's house.

201
00:10:11,979 --> 00:10:13,645
I did what you told me.

202
00:10:13,647 --> 00:10:16,181
Found the bills of sales
of propane, set 'em on fire--

203
00:10:16,183 --> 00:10:19,718
All the evidence destroyed,
just like you asked.

204
00:10:19,720 --> 00:10:21,086
Listen up, lester.

205
00:10:21,088 --> 00:10:23,788
Now the only files left
that can implicate us

206
00:10:23,790 --> 00:10:25,657
In this drug business...

207
00:10:25,659 --> 00:10:27,926
Are right here.

208
00:10:27,928 --> 00:10:30,261
So we have to trust each other

209
00:10:30,263 --> 00:10:33,331
On the security
of those.

210
00:10:35,835 --> 00:10:37,102
Scoot on back to the mortuary

211
00:10:37,104 --> 00:10:38,670
And take care
of freddy denton's corpse.

212
00:10:41,107 --> 00:10:42,907
Julia:
So, what are the odds

213
00:10:42,909 --> 00:10:45,043
That you, just
passing through,

214
00:10:45,045 --> 00:10:46,745
Happen to be here

215
00:10:46,747 --> 00:10:49,080
On the day that
an unprecedented,

216
00:10:49,082 --> 00:10:51,349
Possibly supernatural
event occurred?

217
00:10:51,351 --> 00:10:53,018
God, I swear,
you ask more questions

218
00:10:53,020 --> 00:10:54,653
Than anybody I've ever met.

219
00:10:54,655 --> 00:10:56,921
Well, you know you're
pretty good at evading them.

220
00:10:56,923 --> 00:10:58,690
And asking questions is my job.

221
00:10:58,692 --> 00:11:01,292
That's just your way of keeping
people from asking you anything.

222
00:11:01,294 --> 00:11:03,028
All right.

223
00:11:03,030 --> 00:11:04,696
Your turn.
How does someone

224
00:11:04,698 --> 00:11:07,899
As ambitious as you
end up here in chester's mill?

225
00:11:07,901 --> 00:11:10,902
My husband grew up here.

226
00:11:10,904 --> 00:11:12,904
And, uh...

227
00:11:12,906 --> 00:11:14,906
Circumstances shifted,

228
00:11:14,908 --> 00:11:17,909
And it just made sense for us,

229
00:11:17,911 --> 00:11:21,279
You know, to... Come here
and start over.

230
00:11:27,086 --> 00:11:29,154
That's our dj, phil.

231
00:11:30,990 --> 00:11:32,424
You want to meet him?
Uh, no.

232
00:11:32,426 --> 00:11:34,159
I'll let you guys
get to... Work.

233
00:11:34,161 --> 00:11:38,430
I'm gonna get a bite
to eat at the diner.

234
00:11:39,932 --> 00:11:41,933
Big jim:
Linda? Where are you?

235
00:11:41,935 --> 00:11:44,335
Jim! Jim!

236
00:11:44,337 --> 00:11:45,970
Jim, I'm down here!

237
00:11:45,972 --> 00:11:47,839
The keys.

238
00:11:49,442 --> 00:11:51,109
Where's paul randolph?

239
00:11:51,111 --> 00:11:53,178
He escaped.

240
00:11:54,447 --> 00:11:56,414
Linda? I'd hoped you were
ready for the responsibility

241
00:11:56,416 --> 00:12:00,018
Jim, with all due respect,
I don't need a lecture.

242
00:12:00,020 --> 00:12:01,920
Take a pause.
We have a disturbed fugitive

243
00:12:01,922 --> 00:12:04,255
On the loose.
As councilman,

244
00:12:04,257 --> 00:12:06,491
It is my job to organize
a search party.

245
00:12:06,493 --> 00:12:08,059
Then go do it.

246
00:12:08,061 --> 00:12:10,762
But I'm not gonna wait
for someone else to get hurt.

247
00:12:12,765 --> 00:12:14,466
Damn it, paul. He took a rifle.

248
00:12:14,468 --> 00:12:15,867
Where you going?

249
00:12:15,869 --> 00:12:17,502
Black ridge woods.
He likes to hunt there.

250
00:12:17,504 --> 00:12:19,904
Listen to me. It's too risky.

251
00:12:19,906 --> 00:12:21,773
Jim, I know you like
to control things,

252
00:12:21,775 --> 00:12:23,441
But you do not control me.

253
00:12:26,278 --> 00:12:28,947
Why worry? I bet they got
government scientists

254
00:12:28,949 --> 00:12:31,082
Tapping on that thing,
trying to figure out

255
00:12:31,084 --> 00:12:32,951
How to talk
with us in here.

256
00:12:32,953 --> 00:12:35,487
Maybe they'll figure out
how to get us more bacon.

257
00:12:35,489 --> 00:12:39,357
Bacon's the least
of our worries, roger.

258
00:12:39,359 --> 00:12:41,860
Any sign
of your daughter?

259
00:12:41,862 --> 00:12:44,262
Not since last night.

260
00:12:44,264 --> 00:12:47,065
Alice is out looking for her.

261
00:12:47,067 --> 00:12:49,868
I can't help but think
that it's just another one

262
00:12:49,870 --> 00:12:52,537
Of those seizures
and norrie's laying unconscious

263
00:12:52,539 --> 00:12:54,539
On the side of a road somewhere.

264
00:12:54,541 --> 00:12:56,775
Oh, now, I'm sure
she's fine.

265
00:13:00,412 --> 00:13:02,413
Excuse me, sir. You...

266
00:13:02,415 --> 00:13:05,049
Wouldn't, by any chance,
have seen my daughter?

267
00:13:07,119 --> 00:13:09,320
Your daughter? How's that work?

268
00:13:09,322 --> 00:13:13,458
My partner and I are
a same-sex couple with a child.

269
00:13:13,460 --> 00:13:16,127
Welcome to the
21st century.

270
00:13:16,129 --> 00:13:19,030
What are you doing here
in chester's mill anyway?

271
00:13:19,032 --> 00:13:21,032
We got stuck here

272
00:13:21,034 --> 00:13:23,067
On our way to drop norrie,
our daughter--

273
00:13:23,069 --> 00:13:25,837
Our legitimate daughter--

274
00:13:25,839 --> 00:13:27,972
Off to a nearby
private school.

275
00:13:27,974 --> 00:13:30,942
Oh. The girl's
reformatory, you mean.

276
00:13:32,077 --> 00:13:34,245
Think they can pray
the gay out of her?

277
00:13:35,381 --> 00:13:37,382
Why don't you come
with me, honey?

278
00:13:37,384 --> 00:13:39,517
Let's get you a
cup of coffee.

279
00:13:39,519 --> 00:13:41,886
Authorities outside still
don't know the composition

280
00:13:41,888 --> 00:13:43,521
Or the origin of the dome.

281
00:13:43,523 --> 00:13:46,925
Presumably they'll keep at it
until they get some answers.

282
00:13:48,428 --> 00:13:51,095
I like this symbiotic thing
we got going on, man.

283
00:13:51,097 --> 00:13:53,431
Key to a civilized society
is a well-informed public.

284
00:13:53,433 --> 00:13:55,233
Oh, that
and indoor plumbing.

285
00:13:55,235 --> 00:13:57,468
Oh. I forgot
about indoor plumbing.

286
00:13:57,470 --> 00:13:59,337
Fingers crossed that holds out.

287
00:14:02,308 --> 00:14:05,443
Where's junior off to
in such a hurry?

288
00:14:06,412 --> 00:14:07,512
I don't know.

289
00:14:07,514 --> 00:14:09,447
It's the councilman's
kid, though.

290
00:14:09,449 --> 00:14:12,050
If anyone's got
the inside scoop, it's him.

291
00:14:15,888 --> 00:14:17,388
Junior!

292
00:14:17,390 --> 00:14:19,257
Where you headed?

293
00:14:19,259 --> 00:14:22,360
Just... Going for a hike.

294
00:14:22,362 --> 00:14:25,230
What's with the helmet?
I don't have to answer
your questions.

295
00:14:25,232 --> 00:14:26,564
It's a free country.

296
00:14:32,071 --> 00:14:34,539
Thank you.

297
00:14:34,541 --> 00:14:36,374
Do you mind?

298
00:14:36,376 --> 00:14:38,943
Hey. It's your joint.

299
00:14:38,945 --> 00:14:40,945
All mine, it seems.

300
00:14:40,947 --> 00:14:43,114
Had a girl, angie, working
the lunch counter,

301
00:14:43,116 --> 00:14:45,416
But I haven't seen
her since dome day.

302
00:14:45,418 --> 00:14:47,652
So, how's it been
staying over at julia's?

303
00:14:47,654 --> 00:14:49,554
Nice and comfy?

304
00:14:52,225 --> 00:14:53,558
Small town, kiddo.

305
00:14:53,560 --> 00:14:55,560
It's only gonna get smaller.

306
00:14:55,562 --> 00:14:58,196
Big jim: All right,
listen up, people.

307
00:14:58,198 --> 00:14:59,631
I got an announcement to make.

308
00:15:00,900 --> 00:15:02,433
Former deputy paul randolph

309
00:15:02,435 --> 00:15:04,535
Has escaped police custody.

310
00:15:04,537 --> 00:15:07,305
Just as a precaution,
I'm gonna ask you all to stay

311
00:15:07,307 --> 00:15:09,941
In your homes until
this situation is resolved.

312
00:15:09,943 --> 00:15:12,977
I'm also putting together
a search party, and I'm asking

313
00:15:12,979 --> 00:15:15,313
If any able-bodied men
are keen to join up.

314
00:15:15,315 --> 00:15:16,381
Right here, big jim.

315
00:15:16,383 --> 00:15:17,949
Count me in, too.

316
00:15:17,951 --> 00:15:19,217
All right.

317
00:15:19,219 --> 00:15:23,388
Now, listen, boys, he's already
assaulted two other people,

318
00:15:23,390 --> 00:15:25,390
And he's stolen a mass
of provisions

319
00:15:25,392 --> 00:15:27,325
From casper's department store.

320
00:15:27,327 --> 00:15:28,526
Now, he's on the run,

321
00:15:28,528 --> 00:15:30,194
But there's only so many
places he can hide.

322
00:15:30,196 --> 00:15:32,030
He took a rifle from
the police station,

323
00:15:32,032 --> 00:15:34,065
So bring your firearms.

324
00:15:35,634 --> 00:15:38,169
I don't believe
we've been, uh,

325
00:15:38,171 --> 00:15:39,504
Formally introduced.

326
00:15:39,506 --> 00:15:40,672
I'm, uh, jim rennie.

327
00:15:40,674 --> 00:15:43,074
People around here
call me big jim.

328
00:15:43,076 --> 00:15:45,944
Barbie.
Barbie.

329
00:15:45,946 --> 00:15:48,012
Well, that's kind of
a funny name

330
00:15:48,014 --> 00:15:50,081
For a fellow
with your particular expertise.

331
00:15:52,551 --> 00:15:55,620
I saw you take that gun
off randolph yesterday.

332
00:15:55,622 --> 00:15:58,489
What are you, a bounty hunter
or something?

333
00:16:02,061 --> 00:16:04,295
Ah, just kidding, of course.

334
00:16:04,297 --> 00:16:07,465
This paul randolph's no fish
in a barrel. He was a...

335
00:16:07,467 --> 00:16:10,201
A marine, served
two tours in iraq.

336
00:16:10,203 --> 00:16:11,336
Oh.

337
00:16:11,338 --> 00:16:13,338
Yeah. Won a silver star.

338
00:16:13,340 --> 00:16:15,606
Perfect.

339
00:16:15,608 --> 00:16:17,608
So...

340
00:16:17,610 --> 00:16:20,445
Barbie,

341
00:16:20,447 --> 00:16:22,547
You in or out?

342
00:16:28,420 --> 00:16:30,355
<i>This is phil bushey</i>
<i>with an update</i>

343
00:16:30,357 --> 00:16:32,724
<i>Concerning the ongoing</i>
<i>manhunt in town.</i>

344
00:16:32,726 --> 00:16:34,659
<i>Former deputy paul randolph's</i>
<i>squad car</i>

345
00:16:34,661 --> 00:16:37,395
<i>Has been spotted off the road</i>
<i>at black ridge woods.</i>

346
00:16:37,397 --> 00:16:40,565
<i>All chester's millers</i>
<i>are under an advisory</i>

347
00:16:40,567 --> 00:16:44,435
<i>To stay home until</i>
<i>the situation is resolved.</i>

348
00:16:49,742 --> 00:16:52,010
Looks like he abandoned it.

349
00:16:54,079 --> 00:16:56,147
Fellas, I got something
over here.

350
00:17:02,121 --> 00:17:04,689
Come on. This way.

351
00:17:06,625 --> 00:17:08,693
Hey. Hold on.

352
00:17:10,462 --> 00:17:13,631
This guy's got
military training, right?

353
00:17:13,633 --> 00:17:15,400
That's a dummy trail-- he'd
never do anything that obvious.

354
00:17:15,402 --> 00:17:16,734
Look at this.

355
00:17:16,736 --> 00:17:19,137
These branches here,
they're all broken.

356
00:17:19,139 --> 00:17:21,372
Right there.

357
00:17:23,275 --> 00:17:25,343
Our man came right
through here.

358
00:17:31,283 --> 00:17:33,384
See, I knew you'd be useful.

359
00:18:35,180 --> 00:18:37,248
♪

360
00:18:56,503 --> 00:18:58,803
Do you always eat
standing up?

361
00:18:58,805 --> 00:19:00,538
Animals eat standing up.

362
00:19:03,475 --> 00:19:05,209
Good point, joe.

363
00:19:05,211 --> 00:19:06,811
These are really good.
They're, like, better

364
00:19:06,813 --> 00:19:08,613
Than those amy's breakfast
scramble wraps

365
00:19:08,615 --> 00:19:10,348
My moms buy
at whole foods.

366
00:19:10,350 --> 00:19:11,749
Your moms?

367
00:19:11,751 --> 00:19:16,287
Yeah, my moms, my pops,
you know, like they say.

368
00:19:17,356 --> 00:19:18,389
Where are your parents?

369
00:19:18,391 --> 00:19:20,725
Outside.
My dad drives a rig, so...

370
00:19:20,727 --> 00:19:22,393
He's gone a lot, and...

371
00:19:22,395 --> 00:19:25,296
My mom was in westlake,
the next town over, when...

372
00:19:25,298 --> 00:19:26,497
You know.

373
00:19:26,499 --> 00:19:28,299
What about yours?

374
00:19:28,301 --> 00:19:32,303
I was on my way to visit
my dad and... You know.

375
00:19:32,305 --> 00:19:34,338
He's a musician.

376
00:19:34,340 --> 00:19:36,574
But driving a rig's
pretty cool, too.

377
00:19:37,776 --> 00:19:39,777
Guess we're both
unsupervised, huh?

378
00:19:39,779 --> 00:19:41,445
Ben:
Hey, joe-joe!

379
00:19:44,816 --> 00:19:46,250
These two lovely ladies
were hoping

380
00:19:46,252 --> 00:19:47,652
To take advantage
of your sweet,

381
00:19:47,654 --> 00:19:49,320
Sweet homemade electricity.

382
00:19:49,322 --> 00:19:51,389
My family
doesn't have a gennie.

383
00:19:51,391 --> 00:19:54,292
Mine, neither. And the
music they play on wybs

384
00:19:54,294 --> 00:19:56,327
Is, like, totally schizo.

385
00:20:01,334 --> 00:20:06,270
Uh, I might have mentioned
the generator to a few people.

386
00:20:06,272 --> 00:20:08,773
What about the whole
advisories-to-stay-inside thing?

387
00:20:08,775 --> 00:20:11,442
Dude, it's the apocalypse.
Advisories don't apply.

388
00:20:14,246 --> 00:20:15,980
Nice.

389
00:20:15,982 --> 00:20:17,315
Please tell me you hit that.

390
00:20:19,252 --> 00:20:22,386
Uncool, bro.
Leave a brother hanging.

391
00:20:45,277 --> 00:20:47,812
Big jim:
Just like butch
and sundance, huh?

392
00:20:49,281 --> 00:20:52,717
Barbie:
Are we the good guys
or the bad guys?

393
00:20:52,719 --> 00:20:54,852
You're military, aren't you?

394
00:20:54,854 --> 00:20:57,521
The way you disarmed randolph
and the...

395
00:20:57,523 --> 00:20:59,523
The whole dummy trail business?

396
00:20:59,525 --> 00:21:00,992
No, I was just a grunt.

397
00:21:00,994 --> 00:21:02,493
But you were over there,
weren't you?

398
00:21:02,495 --> 00:21:04,395
You ever been to war?

399
00:21:04,397 --> 00:21:05,930
No.

400
00:21:05,932 --> 00:21:07,765
Never had the privilege.

401
00:21:23,615 --> 00:21:25,316
Paul:
Hey!

402
00:21:25,318 --> 00:21:26,484
Next time, I'll aim higher!

403
00:21:31,290 --> 00:21:34,492
I'm warning you guys,
you better leave me alone!

404
00:21:34,494 --> 00:21:36,560
I don't want to hurt
anyone else!

405
00:21:43,368 --> 00:21:45,469
Ollie, take roger back to town

406
00:21:45,471 --> 00:21:47,505
Before that lunatic
takes another pop at us.

407
00:21:50,542 --> 00:21:53,044
You and me,
we're finishing this thing.

408
00:21:54,013 --> 00:21:57,615
Is it to bring him in, or are we
trying to take him out?

409
00:21:57,617 --> 00:21:58,849
I don't see it makes
a difference

410
00:21:58,851 --> 00:22:00,318
To a guy like you, does it?

411
00:22:00,320 --> 00:22:02,553
What, to a guy like me?

412
00:22:03,622 --> 00:22:05,589
We're losing the light.
Let's move it.

413
00:22:25,410 --> 00:22:27,545
Junior.
I found a way out.

414
00:22:51,470 --> 00:22:52,937
Don't!

415
00:23:00,779 --> 00:23:02,980
You shouldn't have followed me.

416
00:23:10,989 --> 00:23:12,757
Why did you come down here?

417
00:23:14,659 --> 00:23:16,994
I was just hoping
you'd find a way out.

418
00:23:16,996 --> 00:23:19,697
Sorry to let you down.

419
00:23:27,406 --> 00:23:28,839
I hate this thing.

420
00:23:31,611 --> 00:23:34,712
I... Hate you.

421
00:23:59,838 --> 00:24:01,605
Junior...

422
00:24:01,607 --> 00:24:03,607
Are you okay?

423
00:24:03,609 --> 00:24:06,710
No. These...
These tunnels are dangerous.

424
00:24:06,712 --> 00:24:09,847
How can you even find
your way out of the dark?

425
00:24:09,849 --> 00:24:12,483
And they're even more dangerous
with this thing cutting into it.

426
00:24:12,485 --> 00:24:15,219
What if it collapses on us?

427
00:24:15,221 --> 00:24:17,688
People die in here.

428
00:24:17,690 --> 00:24:20,658
I did a story once
on coal miners,

429
00:24:20,660 --> 00:24:23,594
Guys trapped
underground.

430
00:24:23,596 --> 00:24:25,963
You see the way
the flame flickers?

431
00:24:25,965 --> 00:24:28,999
You know which way
the air flows,

432
00:24:29,001 --> 00:24:30,634
You follow it home.

433
00:24:32,204 --> 00:24:34,472
Let's go home.

434
00:24:58,597 --> 00:25:00,698
♪

435
00:25:00,700 --> 00:25:02,266
Ben:
Dude, you're not
gonna believe this.

436
00:25:02,268 --> 00:25:03,834
The guys got

437
00:25:03,836 --> 00:25:05,536
<i>The simpsons movie</i>
<i>going on a loop.</i>

438
00:25:05,538 --> 00:25:07,771
They totally saw
the dome coming.

439
00:25:07,773 --> 00:25:09,807
When can I ask people to leave?

440
00:25:09,809 --> 00:25:11,642
Scarecrow joe.

441
00:25:11,644 --> 00:25:13,911
Nice house party, bro.

442
00:25:13,913 --> 00:25:16,180
Carter. Used to go out
with your sister.

443
00:25:16,182 --> 00:25:18,148
Well, stayed in
more than we went out,

444
00:25:18,150 --> 00:25:19,783
If you know what I mean.

445
00:25:19,785 --> 00:25:21,085
Thanks for inviting us
in, little man.

446
00:25:21,087 --> 00:25:22,686
We'll just make
ourselves at home.

447
00:25:23,822 --> 00:25:25,523
Think about it.

448
00:25:25,525 --> 00:25:26,891
You have a house to yourself.

449
00:25:26,893 --> 00:25:29,527
You could become
the most popular guy in town.

450
00:25:29,529 --> 00:25:30,961
Maybe even get

451
00:25:30,963 --> 00:25:32,263
A girlfriend
out of it.

452
00:25:34,799 --> 00:25:36,267
She digs you.

453
00:25:36,269 --> 00:25:38,102
I've got an instinct
about these things.

454
00:25:38,104 --> 00:25:40,771
Just don't tell her about
that funky seizure you had.

455
00:25:40,773 --> 00:25:42,940
Don't want her
to think you're a spaz.

456
00:25:48,947 --> 00:25:50,681
Total spaz move.

457
00:25:50,683 --> 00:25:51,916
Let's work
on that, dude.

458
00:25:51,918 --> 00:25:54,552
Can you remember
which way we came?

459
00:25:54,554 --> 00:25:56,720
I don't have a lot
of matches left.

460
00:25:56,722 --> 00:26:00,057
We're trapped down here,
we're trapped out there.

461
00:26:00,059 --> 00:26:01,892
What's the difference?

462
00:26:04,229 --> 00:26:07,698
I just wanted
to do something good today.

463
00:26:09,267 --> 00:26:11,702
A man stands up.

464
00:26:11,704 --> 00:26:13,304
A man doesn't screw up.

465
00:26:16,708 --> 00:26:19,109
We all screw up.

466
00:26:19,111 --> 00:26:22,246
We make bad choices.

467
00:26:22,248 --> 00:26:25,849
Tell that to my father.

468
00:26:27,352 --> 00:26:29,887
You want to know how I ended up
in chester's mill?

469
00:26:29,889 --> 00:26:32,656
I was covering the
mayor's race in chicago.

470
00:26:32,658 --> 00:26:33,924
The guy in the lead

471
00:26:33,926 --> 00:26:37,628
Was a real machine politician.

472
00:26:37,630 --> 00:26:39,830
I really wanted
to take him down.

473
00:26:39,832 --> 00:26:41,231
About a week
before the election,

474
00:26:41,233 --> 00:26:44,168
One of my sources
sent me some documents

475
00:26:44,170 --> 00:26:45,669
That showed bribery.

476
00:26:45,671 --> 00:26:47,338
I thought the leaked
docs might be forged,

477
00:26:47,340 --> 00:26:49,707
But I went ahead with
the story anyway.

478
00:26:49,709 --> 00:26:51,976
And it blew up
in my face.

479
00:26:51,978 --> 00:26:54,378
The truth about
my little lie surfaced,

480
00:26:54,380 --> 00:26:58,682
The guy got reelected,
and I was fired

481
00:26:58,684 --> 00:27:00,884
And disgraced.

482
00:27:03,254 --> 00:27:04,922
And now I'm here.

483
00:27:04,924 --> 00:27:08,092
So I know from
screw-ups.

484
00:27:10,061 --> 00:27:12,329
Tell you one
thing, though.

485
00:27:12,331 --> 00:27:16,000
I will never make
that mistake again.

486
00:27:20,639 --> 00:27:22,873
We just keep moving forward.

487
00:27:22,875 --> 00:27:25,843
Carter:
Who needs some juice?

488
00:27:25,845 --> 00:27:27,911
Whoa, hold up, freshie.

489
00:27:27,913 --> 00:27:29,747
Five bucks for five minutes.

490
00:27:29,749 --> 00:27:31,815
Should I do something
about this?

491
00:27:31,817 --> 00:27:33,751
Yeah, and get your face
picasso-ed by a guy

492
00:27:33,753 --> 00:27:35,152
Who's got
25 pounds on you?

493
00:27:36,888 --> 00:27:38,989
He doesn't run
our electricity.

494
00:27:38,991 --> 00:27:40,958
Did you ever take
american history?

495
00:27:40,960 --> 00:27:42,393
Uh, yeah.

496
00:27:42,395 --> 00:27:44,895
So you know about
the sherman antitrust act?

497
00:27:44,897 --> 00:27:46,797
I don't know. Maybe.

498
00:27:46,799 --> 00:27:48,732
Maybe not. 'cause if you had,

499
00:27:48,734 --> 00:27:50,901
You'd know that what
you're doing is illegal.

500
00:27:50,903 --> 00:27:52,236
Monopolies are illegal.

501
00:27:52,238 --> 00:27:54,038
Monopoly's not illegal.

502
00:27:54,040 --> 00:27:56,407
We have the board game
at my house.

503
00:27:56,409 --> 00:28:00,010
Well, then maybe you should go
back to your house.

504
00:28:00,012 --> 00:28:01,445
Play by yourself.

505
00:28:09,220 --> 00:28:11,121
I think I'd rather play
with you, red.

506
00:28:11,123 --> 00:28:12,990
Why don't we
take this upstairs?

507
00:28:12,992 --> 00:28:14,091
I think you should leave.

508
00:28:14,093 --> 00:28:16,060
Oh, I am leaving, little man.

509
00:28:16,062 --> 00:28:17,795
I'm going up
to your sister's room.

510
00:28:17,797 --> 00:28:19,096
I don't think she'd mind.

511
00:28:19,098 --> 00:28:21,999
No. I want you
to leave my house.

512
00:28:23,034 --> 00:28:24,702
Move. Now.

513
00:28:24,704 --> 00:28:26,704
Or this gets ugly fast.

514
00:28:29,308 --> 00:28:30,774
Girl:
The generator blew.

515
00:28:30,776 --> 00:28:33,110
This ain't even close to over,
scarecrow.

516
00:28:44,089 --> 00:28:46,356
Junior:
How many matches
do we have left?

517
00:28:46,358 --> 00:28:48,459
One.

518
00:28:51,329 --> 00:28:54,064
There's a reason for all this:

519
00:28:54,066 --> 00:28:55,766
The dome,

520
00:28:55,768 --> 00:28:58,368
All those people
who died.

521
00:28:58,370 --> 00:29:01,472
This all happened when
that barbie guy showed up.

522
00:29:02,440 --> 00:29:04,108
Sometimes,
when we don't understand

523
00:29:04,110 --> 00:29:07,745
The answer to a thing,
we look for someone to blame.

524
00:29:08,513 --> 00:29:10,414
Oh, I understand.

525
00:29:10,416 --> 00:29:13,350
I understand he attacked
me out of the blue.

526
00:29:15,019 --> 00:29:16,453
See this?

527
00:29:16,455 --> 00:29:19,123
You know how I got that?

528
00:29:19,125 --> 00:29:22,126
Good old barbie.

529
00:29:22,128 --> 00:29:23,894
People think
he's this hero,

530
00:29:23,896 --> 00:29:27,431
But he's a psychopath.

531
00:29:27,433 --> 00:29:30,868
Barbie just attacked you
for no reason?

532
00:29:30,870 --> 00:29:33,203
That's right.

533
00:29:33,205 --> 00:29:35,472
You don't know this guy.

534
00:29:35,474 --> 00:29:38,776
I mean, what's he
really doing here?

535
00:29:40,011 --> 00:29:41,278
Has he been here before?

536
00:29:41,280 --> 00:29:43,313
He has to answer some questions.

537
00:29:50,155 --> 00:29:52,422
What do we do now?

538
00:30:20,485 --> 00:30:22,219
Come on.

539
00:30:22,221 --> 00:30:24,121
I'll give you a ride home.

540
00:30:31,229 --> 00:30:33,997
Barbie:
I think we ought
to call it a day here

541
00:30:33,999 --> 00:30:37,901
Why's that? So we can give
randolph a chance to get away?

542
00:30:37,903 --> 00:30:39,903
Come on, man.
We're sealed in here.

543
00:30:39,905 --> 00:30:41,071
Where the hell's
he gonna go?

544
00:30:41,073 --> 00:30:42,873
I told you we're
finishing this.

545
00:30:42,875 --> 00:30:44,408
Why is that?

546
00:30:44,410 --> 00:30:48,078
So you can show the town
what a big man big jim is?

547
00:30:49,614 --> 00:30:53,016
You ever play
football, barbie?

548
00:30:53,018 --> 00:30:57,221
No. I was never much
of a team sports kind of guy.

549
00:30:58,591 --> 00:31:00,257
I played cornerback.

550
00:31:00,259 --> 00:31:02,125
A lot of smaller
guys play

551
00:31:02,127 --> 00:31:05,362
'cause it requires
speed and agility.

552
00:31:06,931 --> 00:31:10,100
Back in school, we had
this all-state wideout,

553
00:31:10,102 --> 00:31:13,270
A real, uh... A real
showboater, you know?

554
00:31:15,206 --> 00:31:20,544
He called me "big jim," uh,
but as a joke, you know?

555
00:31:20,546 --> 00:31:24,014
Laughing at me.

556
00:31:24,016 --> 00:31:27,351
And one day we, um...
We had to scrimmage,

557
00:31:27,353 --> 00:31:30,287
And he was taunting me,
you know?

558
00:31:30,289 --> 00:31:32,356
"come on, big jim," you know?

559
00:31:32,358 --> 00:31:35,659
"you can't touch me, big jim,"
you know?

560
00:31:37,262 --> 00:31:40,297
So...

561
00:31:40,299 --> 00:31:43,533
I put the mother of all hits
on this punk.

562
00:31:43,535 --> 00:31:46,904
I mean, helmet first,
went in low,

563
00:31:46,906 --> 00:31:50,073
Completely shattered his pelvis.

564
00:31:50,075 --> 00:31:51,909
Guess what.

565
00:31:51,911 --> 00:31:55,545
Big jim wasn't a joke no more.

566
00:31:55,547 --> 00:31:57,414
What does that tell you?

567
00:31:57,416 --> 00:32:02,085
Tells me that being on your team
could be hazardous to my health.

568
00:32:02,087 --> 00:32:05,355
Sometimes an example needs
to be made, you know?

569
00:32:05,357 --> 00:32:07,457
Command respect.

570
00:32:07,459 --> 00:32:09,927
An eye for an eye.

571
00:32:13,965 --> 00:32:15,699
Jim?

572
00:32:22,674 --> 00:32:24,174
I'll kill him...

573
00:32:24,176 --> 00:32:26,343
Just like he was gonna kill me.

574
00:32:26,345 --> 00:32:28,478
Nobody wants to kill
anybody here.
He said it himself.

575
00:32:28,480 --> 00:32:30,380
An eye for an eye, right?

576
00:32:31,182 --> 00:32:33,283
Make an example out of me.

577
00:32:33,285 --> 00:32:35,686
Drop your weapon now.

578
00:32:38,056 --> 00:32:39,489
I said drop your
weapon now...

579
00:32:57,343 --> 00:32:59,209
Big jim:
Evening to you, lester.

580
00:32:59,211 --> 00:33:01,211
I'm sorry to say
we brought you another customer.

581
00:33:01,213 --> 00:33:03,280
Coggins:
I'm not finished
with deputy denton yet.

582
00:33:03,282 --> 00:33:05,148
Patching a wound takes time.

583
00:33:05,150 --> 00:33:06,583
Paul randolph
needs your help, too.

584
00:33:08,019 --> 00:33:11,688
The lord never gives us
more than we can handle, rev.

585
00:33:14,026 --> 00:33:15,559
You clean?

586
00:33:15,561 --> 00:33:17,561
Absolutely, jim.

587
00:33:17,563 --> 00:33:20,497
Any red you see in my eyes,
that's overwork, nothing else.

588
00:33:20,499 --> 00:33:22,699
Let's keep it that way.

589
00:33:27,305 --> 00:33:29,272
Hey, would you mind
waiting at the car?

590
00:33:29,274 --> 00:33:30,674
I need to talk
to linda.

591
00:33:30,676 --> 00:33:32,743
Yeah. Sure.

592
00:33:34,645 --> 00:33:37,647
I'm sorry.

593
00:33:37,649 --> 00:33:39,716
For questioning your dedication

594
00:33:39,718 --> 00:33:42,552
Or if, in any way,
I insinuated that...

595
00:33:42,554 --> 00:33:45,422
You weren't capable
of filling duke's shoes.

596
00:33:48,092 --> 00:33:50,360
He'd be proud of you, you know.

597
00:33:50,362 --> 00:33:53,463
Fact, I bet he's
up there right now,

598
00:33:53,465 --> 00:33:55,265
Eating roast beef
and mashed potatoes

599
00:33:55,267 --> 00:33:58,535
With the big guy,
looking down on you and smiling.

600
00:34:00,304 --> 00:34:04,307
We're gonna do big things,
you and I.

601
00:34:04,309 --> 00:34:08,512
First, we got to get you
some deputies.

602
00:34:08,514 --> 00:34:11,348
There's a new sheriff
in town.

603
00:34:11,350 --> 00:34:14,418
And her name
is linda esquivel.

604
00:34:25,229 --> 00:34:27,230
Um, so...

605
00:34:27,232 --> 00:34:30,233
I was wondering
if maybe we could...

606
00:34:30,235 --> 00:34:34,104
Keep what happened today
between us.

607
00:34:37,842 --> 00:34:39,843
You know, we all
have secrets, junior.

608
00:34:46,384 --> 00:34:48,452
You can call me james.

609
00:34:51,456 --> 00:34:55,125
I never did like
being called junior anyways.

610
00:34:58,262 --> 00:35:00,564
I'm guessing
you're a scotch guy.

611
00:35:00,566 --> 00:35:02,632
you don't miss much, do you?

612
00:35:02,634 --> 00:35:04,701
Straight up,
of course.

613
00:35:30,862 --> 00:35:32,863
Uh, maybe we should do this
another time.

614
00:35:35,900 --> 00:35:37,834
It's a small town, son.

615
00:35:39,505 --> 00:35:41,538
And we all support the team.

616
00:35:47,178 --> 00:35:49,546
What was that about?

617
00:35:49,548 --> 00:35:52,282
Long story.

618
00:36:00,458 --> 00:36:02,526
♪

619
00:36:42,633 --> 00:36:45,702
What kind of trouble
you been getting into?

620
00:36:47,505 --> 00:36:49,372
No trouble.

621
00:36:49,374 --> 00:36:50,840
I went down into
the cement works

622
00:36:50,842 --> 00:36:52,509
And tried to
find a way out.

623
00:36:52,511 --> 00:36:54,644
failed, huh?

624
00:36:55,613 --> 00:36:57,447
Yeah.

625
00:36:57,449 --> 00:36:59,783
The dome goes straight through.

626
00:36:59,785 --> 00:37:01,451
Well, of course it does.

627
00:37:01,453 --> 00:37:03,653
You didn't think
it'd be that easy, did you?

628
00:37:06,490 --> 00:37:08,491
What were you doing
with that barbie guy?

629
00:37:08,493 --> 00:37:09,793
That's none of your business.

630
00:37:09,795 --> 00:37:11,595
I'll make it my business.

631
00:37:11,597 --> 00:37:14,331
Not unless I tell you to.

632
00:37:14,333 --> 00:37:17,234
Don't you worry
your head over barbie.

633
00:37:18,336 --> 00:37:20,670
Let the grown-ups do their job.

634
00:37:24,643 --> 00:37:27,711
Drink your milk,
now, junior.

635
00:37:36,621 --> 00:37:38,455
What are you doing?
I don't know.

636
00:37:38,457 --> 00:37:40,457
Um, maybe I can fix it.

637
00:37:40,459 --> 00:37:41,591
Really?

638
00:37:41,593 --> 00:37:43,460
That thing blew up
like the death star.

639
00:37:43,462 --> 00:37:44,961
Yeah, but the empire
rebuilt the death star

640
00:37:44,963 --> 00:37:46,563
In <i>the return of the jedi.</i>

641
00:37:46,565 --> 00:37:48,698
It was almost
fully operational.

642
00:37:48,700 --> 00:37:50,600
I like nerds.

643
00:37:50,602 --> 00:37:51,901
carolyn:
Norrie?

644
00:37:51,903 --> 00:37:53,637
oh, god.

645
00:37:53,639 --> 00:37:55,505
Norrie, are you here...?

646
00:37:57,643 --> 00:37:59,009
Carolyn, how did
you find me?

647
00:37:59,011 --> 00:38:00,944
Something goes boom
in a small town,

648
00:38:00,946 --> 00:38:02,612
Parents tend to know.

649
00:38:03,648 --> 00:38:04,848
Let's go.

650
00:38:04,850 --> 00:38:07,317
Wh-who is this lady?

651
00:38:08,286 --> 00:38:11,454
She's one of my moms.

652
00:38:11,456 --> 00:38:13,523
One of your...
Okay, I guess
there's just

653
00:38:13,525 --> 00:38:15,959
Some things I didn't
want you to know about me.

654
00:38:19,463 --> 00:38:21,498
But, hey...

655
00:38:21,500 --> 00:38:24,467
Thanks for almost
getting beat up for me.

656
00:38:24,469 --> 00:38:26,770
That was...

657
00:38:26,772 --> 00:38:28,638
Kind of chivalrous.

658
00:38:34,679 --> 00:38:36,646
Oh, my god. Norrie?
What happened?

659
00:38:36,648 --> 00:38:38,081
Joe and norrie:
The pink stars are falling.
Carolyn: Norrie!

660
00:38:38,083 --> 00:38:40,550
The pink stars are falling
in lines.
Norrie.

661
00:38:40,552 --> 00:38:42,619
Joe and norrie:
The pink stars are falling
in lines.

662
00:38:42,621 --> 00:38:44,688
Norrie!
The pink stars are falling.

663
00:38:44,690 --> 00:38:46,589
Norrie!
The pink stars
are falling.

664
00:38:46,591 --> 00:38:47,691
Carolyn:
Get help!
The pink stars

665
00:38:47,693 --> 00:38:48,758
Are falling.
Go!

666
00:38:48,760 --> 00:38:50,360
The pink stars are...

667
00:38:59,737 --> 00:39:01,805
Angie?

668
00:39:03,708 --> 00:39:05,809
Did you make it under?

669
00:39:05,811 --> 00:39:08,678
Uh-uh. Uh...

670
00:39:11,916 --> 00:39:14,918
There's no way out.

671
00:39:14,920 --> 00:39:16,720
I made sure of it.

672
00:39:19,790 --> 00:39:21,791
What happened to your hands?

673
00:39:23,628 --> 00:39:25,695
I beat on that thing.

674
00:39:27,631 --> 00:39:29,366
Stood up

675
00:39:29,368 --> 00:39:32,369
And beat on it until the lights
went out, angie.

676
00:39:35,940 --> 00:39:38,007
'cause I love you.

677
00:39:56,160 --> 00:39:58,561
♪

678
00:40:13,711 --> 00:40:16,780
So, that comment that you made
about me running into the fire

679
00:40:16,782 --> 00:40:18,748
Was aggravatingly hypocritical.

680
00:40:18,750 --> 00:40:21,151
No, especially
considering the adventure

681
00:40:21,153 --> 00:40:23,887
You went on today
with big jim.

682
00:40:23,889 --> 00:40:26,423
Yeah, but there's a difference
between me and you.

683
00:40:26,425 --> 00:40:27,824
How so?

684
00:40:28,793 --> 00:40:32,128
I take off after the fire's out.

685
00:40:32,130 --> 00:40:33,696
I mean, at least,

686
00:40:33,698 --> 00:40:35,865
When there's somewhere
to take off to.

687
00:40:40,905 --> 00:40:42,906
You bruised your knuckles.

688
00:40:44,809 --> 00:40:46,142
Yeah.

689
00:40:46,144 --> 00:40:47,877
I bruised my knuckles.

690
00:40:48,946 --> 00:40:50,914
And you really
were just passing through

691
00:40:50,916 --> 00:40:52,715
Chester's mill?

692
00:40:52,717 --> 00:40:54,884
No connection
to anyone here in town?

693
00:40:56,821 --> 00:40:58,555
Nope.

694
00:41:01,625 --> 00:41:03,226
Good night, julia.

695
00:41:27,952 --> 00:41:30,019
